      • onUserSubmit

        public int onUserSubmit()
        Processes user submission, validates and parses the amount to order as an integer. If the user's input is not a valid positive integer, displays an error message and sets an error border around the input field.
        Returns:
        the validated input amount as an integer. Returns -1 if the input is invalid.

      • onUserSubmit2

        public double onUserSubmit2()
        Processes user submission, validates and parses the amount to order as a double. Similar to onUserSubmit, but allows for decimal inputs representing quantities.
        Returns:
        the validated input amount as a double. Returns -1.0 if the input is invalid.

      • getIngredientUsageReport

        public javax.swing.table.DefaultTableModel getIngredientUsageReport​(java.sql.Date startDate,
                                                                    java.sql.Date endDate)
        Retrieves a report on ingredient usage between specified start and end dates. Generates a DefaultTableModel containing data about ingredient usage which is suitable for display in a JTable. Ingredient Usage = sales report
        Parameters:
        startDate - The start date for the report period.
        endDate - The end date for the report period.
        Returns:
        a DefaultTableModel with ingredient usage data.

      • getIngredientReport

        public javax.swing.table.DefaultTableModel getIngredientReport​(java.sql.Date startDate)
        Retrieves a report on ingredients that are less than 10% of their total quantity since the specified start date to the current date. This can be used to identify ingredients that are nearing depletion.
        Parameters:
        startDate - The start date for checking ingredient depletion.
        Returns:
        a DefaultTableModel with data on ingredients nearing depletion.
